race.comment: SADLERS SYMPHONY (11) made sharp improvement at his second outing when stepping up to 1765m at Geelong, finding the line strongly to just miss by a nose off an encouraging debut at Hamilton. Looks a real staying type so should be suited getting to 2000m now and looks to have found a race lacking depth. IMMORTAL ROSE (9) was disappointing here second up off a nice return. She's lightly raced and open to improvement but will need to turn things around quickly. BERNIE BEEL (1) is a 44 start maiden but going better than ever, second last time out. Another placing is on the cards. HONEYJOY (8) was sound fresh over 1400m and could improve.
